    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="369"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.00R/5–551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Administrator, Economic Cooperation Administration</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foster</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                            Indonesia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-05T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 5, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss> 252. This is joint State–<gloss
                        target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> cable. Fol will answer your recent letter
                        queries<note n="1" xml:id="d369fn1">Not printed.</note> re status <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> program.</p>
                <p>As result extensive discussions Dept and <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>,
                    full agreement reached concerning Indonesia program for remainder <gloss
                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 51 and <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 52 as
                    follows: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>For <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 51 total program $9.95 million.
                            This represents approx $3.7 million above amount already obligated,
                            distributed in fields public health ($2.3 million) agriculture,
                            forestry, fisheries ($.9 million), industry ($.5 million). <gloss
                                target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 51 program this size will require approx
                            $1.9 million in addition to unobligated funds presently
                            available.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>For <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 52, an econ aid program of the
                            gen character of the present program with special emphasis on technical
                            assistance. TA personnel would not necessarily be tied to particular
                            projects, and would be furnished on a contract basis or directly by
                                <gloss target="#t_STEM1">STEM</gloss> depending on Indonesian wishes
                            and <gloss target="#t_STEM1">STEM</gloss> judgment.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>The <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 52 program proposed to Bureau
                            $10.4 million in grant aid, distributed in fol fields by way of
                            illustration: Public Health ($3.9 million); agri forestry, fisheries
                            ($3.7 million); Transportation, communications, power and public works
                            ($410 thousand); engineering services ($.6 million); Information ($.2
                            million); Education ($.3 million) and Public Administration and
                            Technical Assistance ($1.6 million). Figures in parens exceed $10.4
                            total due to inclusion some of TA under public health, transportation,
                            and agriculture categories as well as under public administration and
                            TA.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Dept and <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> in full accord re
                            desirability programming additional loans probably <gloss
                                target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                                >Indo</gloss> if and as study of individual projects so warrants. To
                            this end, appropriate Ex agencies currently discussing suitable
                            mechanism for extending program loans in <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                                >FY</gloss> 52 to <gloss target="#t_SEA1">SEA</gloss> countries
                            generally, such loans to be integrated with and coordinated as part of
                            same program US economic and technical aid for which grant aid being
                            extended. Will advise you further as these discussions progress.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Foregoing recommendations fully cleared throughout Ex agencies and presented to
                    Budget Bureau on April 13.<note n="2" xml:id="d369fn2">See the first footnote 1,
                            <ref target="#pg_636">p. 636</ref>.</note> No indication yet as <pb
                        facs="0664" n="646" xml:id="pg_646"/> to action to be taken by Bureau.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d369fn3">In telegram <gloss target="#t_Ecato1">Ecato</gloss>
                        324 to Djakarta, May 29, Mr. Shannon McCune, Acting Chief, <gloss
                            target="#t_STEM1">STEM</gloss> Mission in Indonesia, was informed that
                        the Bureau of the Budget had approved a figure of $8,000,000 for economic
                        grant aid to Indonesia (<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> Cable Files:
                            <gloss target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> Acc. 53 A 278, Box 77).</note>
                    Forwarding by pouch documentation and elaboration of <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss> 52 program as presented to Budget Bureau.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d369fn4">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
